-- Reichenbach ‘More Optimistic Than Ever’ on Greece, Passauer Says
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2012-03-24T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/reichenbach-more-optimistic-than-ever-on-greece-passauer-says.html
Horst Reichenbach, who heads the
European Union task force on rebuilding  Greece ’s economy, said
he is “more optimistic than ever,”  Passauer Neue Presse 
reported, citing an interview.  There have been improvements controlling pension fraud and
expenditures, Reichenbach told the newspaper. He added that he
hopes to collect 2 billion euros ($2,65 billion) in tax
receivables this year, Passauer Neue Presse reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Dusseldorf via 
